Demo POC Setup:
Date: 29, June 2026
===================
Open 3 terminals, On all terminals:
~/aiwork/vios/repo/rmsai-relay
conda activate rmsrelay_env

Terminal A:
under infra directory

docker compose restart
docker ps => ensure qdrant, redis, neo4j

under project dir
uv run python -m cli.voice_worker dev

Terminal B:
for generating hdf5 and publishing

uv run python external/ecgtranscnn/scripts/generate_inference_data.py
uv run python -m cli.ingest     --file data/inference/<REPLACE>.h5  --checkpoint external/ecgtranscnn/models/noise_robust/best_model.pt     --emit bus --stream rmsai.events

Terminal C:
for consuming events from redis -

uv run python -m cli.consume --channel voice --caller livekit --transport webrtc --once

Copy the URL and Token from any event in the terminal log. Every event produces a new Token.

Web Browser:
~~~~~~~~~~~~
https://meet.livekit.io/?tab=custom
Paste the URL and the Token and Connect

Give permissions to MIC and Unmute the Mic
Speak the PIN: 1234 (Configurable in .env)

Q&A general:
~~~~~~~~~~~~
List all patients, bed number, unit or ward who had critical events in the last 24 hours
List positive patient events that were reported in the last x minutes.
What is the status of patient events reported on Bed xx. show the timnestamp, reported event, false positive?, actual condition. etc
Get the event analysis report for patient or Bed xx in Unit/Ward.
What was the vitals at the time of the specific event for patient in Bed. (retriveing specific data from the report)
Provide an action Item list for all outstanding actions need to be taken for patients
What is the treatment care protocol for patient Bed side x with the last reported event
From the data, do you see any pattern for age, geneder, co-morbidites or symptoms are leading to specific event
Show me the ECG strips for the patient with the last reported specific event (AFib etc).
Show me the HR and BP trend for the patient with the last reported Tachycardia event.
Show all patients who have a AFIB event.
Show all patients who have an AFib event
Show me the HR and BP trend for the patient with the last reported Tachycardia event
Show me the ECG strips for the patient with the last reported AFib event
